on shift all the buildings in the North? ) Negative value indicates south\n6. Theta -> Rotation Angle (shows whether the whole sketchmap is rotated by a certail angle)\n7. phi -> scale (shows whether the things in sketchmap are larger or smaller than the basemap.)\n\nThese measures constitutes BDR (Bi - Dimensional Regression).\n\nBDR always works on 2 points or in this case polygons (which are also being denoted by points in this case). \n\nNow, these measures are ran individualy on a pair (one point in Basemap and another in sketchmap) and then all of these values are averaged by all of the buildings in the sketchmap. \n\n\n","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"import geopandas as gpd\nimport json\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T12:23:39.532345Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T12:23:39.532961Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T12:23:40.385597Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-16T12:23:39.532923Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-16T12:23:40.383653Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":2},{"cell_type":"code","source":"bsm_feat = gpd.read_file(\"/kaggle/input/datasets/ajayuchana/stechmap-bdr-test/basemap.jpg.geojson\")\nbsm_landmarks  = bsm_feat[bsm_feat['feat_type'] == 'Landmark']\n\n\nprint(bsm_landmarks)\nbsm_landmarks.plot()","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-04-16T12:23:40.386924Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-04-16T12:23:40.387427Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-04-16T12:23:41.093644Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-04-16T12:23:40.387397Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-04-16T12:23:41.092875Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"    id isRoute feat_type  selected  aligned    otype  RouteSeqOrder  missing  \\\n24  24    None  Landmark     False     True  Polygon            NaN      NaN   \n25  25    None  Landmark     False     True  Polygon            NaN      NaN   \n26  26    None  Landmark     False     True  Polygon            NaN      NaN 